div.p:
Thou seest now, that we can come near the Enemies Country;
though even That doth seldom happen: But we can't get into it,
for the Heart-blood of us. Though we desire it above all Things;
and though we want neither Strength, nor Courage, nor Conduct.
And therefore thou may'st be satisfied, as well as I, That
the Devil has hinder'd us, and that we have been bewitch'd.
